  "text": "## OpenTelemetry Span Creation Patterns Across Prometheus and Grafana\n\n### Tracer Initialization\n\nBoth projects use OpenTelemetry SDK for tracing initialization with different approaches:\n\n**Prometheus** (prometheus/prometheus:tracing/tracing.go): The `buildTracerProvider()` function (lines 129-175) initializes a TracerProvider using `tracesdk.NewTracerProvider()` with:\n- `WithBatcher(exp)` for batching exports\n- `WithSampler(tracesdk.ParentBased(...))` for sampling configuration\n- `WithResource(res)` for resource attributes\nThe Manager type (lines 42-49) manages the tracer provider lifecycle with `ApplyConfig()` method that calls `otel.SetTracerProvider(tp)` (line 102).\n\n**Grafana** (github.com/grafana/grafana:pkg/storage/unified/sql/db/otel/otel_test.go): Test setup shows `sdktrace.NewTracerProvider()` (line 295) with:\n- `WithSyncer(exporter)` for in-memory exports during testing\n- `WithSpanProcessor(recorder)` for span recording (pkg/apiserver/endpoints/filters/tracing_log_test.go:25)\n- `WithSampler(sdktrace.AlwaysSample())` for always-on sampling\n\n### Span Start/End Patterns\n\n**Prometheus pattern**: Uses `otel.Tracer(\"\").Start(ctx, spanName)` returning both context and span:\n- storage/remote/queue_manager.go:2298: `ctx, span := otel.Tracer(\"\").Start(ctx, \"Remote Send Batch\")`\n- rules/group.go:515: `ctx, sp := otel.Tracer(\"\").Start(ctx, \"rule\")`\n- storage/remote/client.go:402: `ctx, span := otel.Tracer(\"\").Start(ctx, \"Remote Read\", trace.WithSpanKind(trace.SpanKindClient))`\n- scrape/scrape.go:748: `ctx, span := otel.Tracer(\"\").Start(ctx, \"Scrape\", trace.WithSpanKind(trace.SpanKindClient))`\n\nAll spans use `defer span.End()` for cleanup.\n\n**Grafana pattern**: Uses either `tracer.Start()` (injected) or `tracing.Start()` helper:\n- pkg/bus/bus.go:55: `_, span := b.tracer.Start(ctx, \"bus - \"+msgName)` followed by `defer span.End()`\n- pkg/expr/graph.go:127: `c, span := s.tracer.Start(c, \"SSE.ExecuteNode\")`\n- pkg/modules/tracing/listener.go:41: `spanCtx, span := tracing.Start(l.ctx, l.serviceName)`\n\n### Span Attribute Setting\n\n**Prometheus**:\n- storage/remote/queue_manager.go:2299-2311: Sets multiple attributes with `span.SetAttributes()` using type-specific constructors:\n  - `attribute.Int(\"request_size\", sc.reqSize)`\n  - `attribute.String(\"remote_name\", remoteName)`\n- rules/group.go:516: `sp.SetAttributes(attribute.String(\"name\", rule.Name()))`\n- promql/engine.go:1922: `span.SetAttributes(attribute.String(\"operation\", ss.ShortString()))`\n\n**Grafana**:\n- pkg/bus/bus.go:58: `span.SetAttributes(attribute.String(\"msg\", msgName))`\n- pkg/expr/graph.go:128-131: Multiple attributes including `StringSlice` type:\n  - `span.SetAttributes(attribute.String(\"node.refId\", node.RefID()))`\n  - `span.SetAttributes(attribute.StringSlice(\"node.inputRefIDs\", inputRefIDs))`\n- pkg/modules/tracing/listener.go:76-82: Building attributes slice and setting with variadic call\n  - `span.SetAttributes(attributes...)`\n\n### Span Error Recording\n\n**Grafana** demonstrates comprehensive error handling:\n- pkg/modules/tracing/listener.go:92-96: Error pattern in `endSpan()`:\n  ```go\n  if err != nil {\n    l.stateSpan.SetStatus(codes.Error, err.Error())\n    l.stateSpan.RecordError(err)\n  } else {\n    l.stateSpan.SetStatus(codes.Ok, \"\")\n  }\n  ```\n- pkg/tsdb/tempo/metrics_stream.go:81-82: Direct error handling:\n  - `span.RecordError(err)`\n  - `span.SetStatus(codes.Error, err.Error())`\n- pkg/registry/apis/dashboard/datasources.go:50-51: Error attribute and recording:\n  - `span.SetAttributes(attribute.String(\"error\", err.Error()))`\n  - `span.RecordError(err)`\n\n**Prometheus**: No explicit error recording found in the primary span patterns; errors are typically logged separately.\n\n### Additional Options Patterns\n\n- **span.WithSpanKind()**: Both prometheus/prometheus:storage/remote/client.go:402 and scrape/scrape.go:748 use `trace.WithSpanKind(trace.SpanKindClient)` to mark client spans\n- **Span context propagation**: Grafana's listener.go demonstrates nested span context passing and parent-child relationships\n- **Semantic conventions**: prometheus/prometheus references semconv for HTTP attributes (semconv.HTTPResendCount)\n\n### Key Differences\n\n1. **Tracer source**: Prometheus uses global `otel.Tracer(\"\")` while Grafana uses injected `tracer` field or `tracing.Start()` helper\n2. **Error handling**: Grafana explicitly records errors with `RecordError()` and `SetStatus()`, Prometheus does not\n3. **Attribute types**: Both support type-specific attribute constructors; Grafana also uses `StringSlice` for list attributes\n4. **Sampling**: Prometheus uses ratio-based sampling (ParentBased with TraceIDRatioBased), Grafana tests use AlwaysSample\n"
}

